annotationA: Vacuolar protein sorting 37B, isoform A; It is involved in the biological process described with: endosome transport via multivesicular body sorting pathway
annotationB: Vacuolar protein sorting 24 is an essential subunit of ESCRT-III, one of the endosomal sorting complexes required for transport (ESCRT). It is involved in membrane remodeling in diverse cellular processes, such as multi-vesicular body biogenesis, cytokinesis and virus budding; Belongs to the SNF7 family
